<item>
 <title> China is Leaving the U.S. Behind on Clean Energy Investment</title>
 <link>http://www.chinafaqs.org/blog-posts/china-leaving-us-behind-clean-energy-investment</link>
 <description>&lt;div class=&quot;field field-type-filefield field-field-image&quot;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;field-items&quot;&gt;
            &lt;div class=&quot;field-item odd&quot;&gt;
                    &lt;img src=&quot;http://www.chinafaqs.org/files/chinainfo/imagecache/news-image/Solar%20panel%20China.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; title=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;180&quot; height=&quot;120&quot; class=&quot;imagecache imagecache-news-image imagecache-default imagecache-news-image_default&quot;/&gt;        &lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;field field-type-text field-field-author&quot;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;field-items&quot;&gt;
            &lt;div class=&quot;field-item odd&quot;&gt;
                    Joel Jaeger, Paul Joffe, and Ranping Song        &lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;This post &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.wri.org/blog/2017/01/china-leaving-us-behind-clean-energy-investment&quot;&gt;originally appeared&lt;/a&gt; on WRI&amp;#8217;s Insights blog.&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As 2017 begins, China is poised to leap ahead of the United States on clean energy to become the most important player in the global market. Last year, China increased its foreign investment in renewables by 60 percent to reach a record $32 billion, according to &lt;a href=&quot;http://ieefa.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Chinas-Global-Renewable-Energy-Expansion_January-2017.pdf&quot;&gt;a new report&lt;/a&gt; from the Institute for Energy Economics and Financial Analysis. This includes 11 new overseas investment deals worth more than $1 billion each.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.chinafaqs.org/blog-posts/china-leaving-us-behind-clean-energy-investment&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;read more&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
